       Developmental Disabilities: An Update for Health Professionals

                             Return to Calendar
            Date/Time Friday, March 1, 2002   (7:30 AM - 5:30 PM)
                Saturday, March 2, 2002   (7:30 AM - 5:30 PM)
                         Location San Francisco, CA
               Address University of California San Francisco
                      Laurel Heights Conference Center
                           3333 California Street
                              San Francisco, CA
                Sponsor Department of Developmental Services
     Who Should Attend Physicians, nurses, allied health professionals,
                           interns, and residents
                                  CEU 17.5
    Description A 2-day Continuing Medical Education Course Presented by
        University of California San Francisco School of Medicine and
    University of California San Diego School of Medicine. Comprehensive
   program that should provide a useful and practical update as well as an
     overview of relevant information for those involved in the care of
                individuals with developmental disabilities.
             Cost Contact sources listed below for information.
      Registration Information Office of Continuing Medical Education,
                             Registration Office
                 UCSF Box 0742, San Francisco, CA 94143-0742
                          Registration Web Address
              www.som.ucsf.edu/som/education/cme/cal/#march2002
                          Telephone (415) 476-5808
                               Accommodations/
    Hotel Information Maxwell Hotel, 386 Geary Street, San Francisco, CA
                               (888) 734-6299
              Laurel Inn 444 Presidio Avenue, San Francisco, CA
                               (800) 552-8735
                  Special rates available for both hotels.
             Further Information $250 for Practicing Physicians
    $125 for Nurses, Allied Health Professionals, Interns, and Residents
                     Course Information: (415) 476-6127.
